But I still make sure
she gets her AARP catalogue

02:43.511 --> 02:45.377
to remind her that she old.

02:45.379 --> 02:46.912
Ohh, you a messy bish.

02:46.914 --> 02:48.314
I don't play.

02:49.984 --> 02:51.651
Y'all...

02:52.281 --> 02:53.653
What's wrong? What's going on?

02:53.655 --> 02:56.788
Roller just stopped me from
pulling a gun on Mac and Melba.

02:56.790 --> 02:59.191
- What are you talking about?
- They got Dean.

02:59.193 --> 03:01.060
- Kidnapped?
- He might as well be.

03:01.062 --> 03:03.128
I mean, they... they in his mind.

03:03.130 --> 03:05.331
- Hey, Sheray.
- Yeah, she's right.

03:05.333 --> 03:06.866
Dean is trippin'.

03:06.868 --> 03:09.134
This fool jumped outta the car last night

03:09.136 --> 03:11.603
and went back to the casino
just to play mahjong.

03:11.605 --> 03:13.133
What do they want from him?

03:13.135 --> 03:14.874
- What can we do?
- I don't know.

03:14.876 --> 03:16.275
Be still. You're about to mess it up.

03:16.277 --> 03:18.143
Now, calm down.
We can think of something.

03:18.145 --> 03:20.212
I feel like I'm losing him,
and I don't know what to do.

03:20.214 --> 03:22.081
His stuff is still back at the motel.

03:22.083 --> 03:23.749
He's got to come back eventually.

03:23.751 --> 03:25.284
Come on, bright idea.

03:25.286 --> 03:28.020
You coming with me. We'll be back.

03:28.022 --> 03:30.690
Hey, if y'all need me
to jack somebody's mail, now,

03:30.692 --> 03:32.291
let me know!

03:34.562 --> 03:36.295
I don't play that.

03:37.117 --> 03:41.705
Here's one thing I know...
Blood doesn't make a family.

03:42.036 --> 03:43.903
In fact, I would go so far as to say

03:43.905 --> 03:46.238
that your family has held you back.

03:46.240 --> 03:48.107
You're like a majestic golden eagle

03:48.109 --> 03:50.623
that somebody has locked in a cage,

03:50.625 --> 03:53.045
and your sister and her friends,
they're your captors.

03:53.047 --> 03:55.915
They're feeding you scraps
of rotten meat.

03:55.917 --> 03:58.650
You know, you eat that shit long
enough, it starts to taste good.

03:58.652 --> 04:00.853
I-I-I think you're using an analogy.

04:00.855 --> 04:03.455
Are... Are you saying
that I-I'm being silenced,

04:03.457 --> 04:06.192
like one of those sister wives
in a prairie dress?

04:06.194 --> 04:08.728
Your real family is a spiritual one,

04:08.730 --> 04:11.463
not one ordained by a birth certificate.

04:11.465 --> 04:12.732
Okay.

04:12.734 --> 04:14.867
Yes, your... your turn.

04:17.738 --> 04:20.672
Hey. What's the word, Polly Bird?

04:20.673 --> 04:22.742
Oh, hey, Roller.

04:22.744 --> 04:24.143
Um, you know, this little birdie's

04:24.145 --> 04:26.078
doing just fine... tweet tweet.

04:26.080 --> 04:28.548
You eatin' the soul out them shrimps.

04:28.550 --> 04:30.817
What's wrong, Polly? You a'ight?

04:31.753 --> 04:33.340
No.

04:34.222 --> 04:36.355
He's gone.

04:36.357 --> 04:38.490
I let him get away.

04:38.492 --> 04:39.691
Who, Dr. Ken?

04:39.693 --> 04:41.264
No, not Ken.

04:41.829 --> 04:43.563
I mean, he's sweet
and everything, but, no,

04:43.565 --> 04:45.765
- this was a real bad boy.
- Mm.

04:45.767 --> 04:48.167
- Yeah, he was good-lookin', too.
- Mm.

04:48.169 --> 04:50.035
But, um...

04:50.037 --> 04:52.317
I found out, you know, he was...

04:53.174 --> 04:54.173
He was killin' people.

04:54.175 --> 04:56.976
Pbht. You kicked him to the curb?

04:56.978 --> 04:58.978
Yeah. He's a murderer.

04:58.980 --> 05:01.118
Don't mean he's a bad guy.

05:01.849 --> 05:04.116
So you think I made a mistake?

05:04.118 --> 05:06.118
Maybe I should just go back to Bayside

05:06.120 --> 05:08.187
- and tell him I was wrong.
- Hold on one second.

05:08.189 --> 05:09.855
This guy work for Mac and Melba?

05:09.857 --> 05:11.857
Uh... what?

05:11.859 --> 05:14.526
Oh. No. No, no.
Uh, never mind, never mind.

05:14.528 --> 05:16.395
- Rewind.
- Rewind.

05:16.397 --> 05:18.530
Double rewind, Polly Bird.
You can't see this man.

05:18.532 --> 05:20.532
But you said you thought
maybe he wasn't a bad guy.

05:20.534 --> 05:23.803
Well, he is 'cause he's killin'
for those casino folks.

05:23.805 --> 05:26.606
Polly, you go and find yourself
a rough neck.

05:26.608 --> 05:27.807
We out there, baby.

05:27.809 --> 05:29.425
It's not the same.

05:32.480 --> 05:35.281
He's not gonna be happy about this.

05:35.283 --> 05:38.550
He hasn't been happy about
anything that I've done lately.

05:38.552 --> 05:39.952
But he needs this.

05:39.954 --> 05:42.955
The only choice we have is
for y'all to move in with me.

05:42.957 --> 05:44.824
I keep telling myself

05:44.826 --> 05:46.826
he's just obsessed with something new,

05:46.828 --> 05:49.354
like he was with stripping
and body building, but this?

05:49.356 --> 05:51.631
Mnh-mnh. This is more than that.

05:51.633 --> 05:53.299
Dean needs me.

05:53.301 --> 05:55.101
He has always needed me.

05:55.103 --> 05:56.969
And that ain't gonna change just 'cause

05:56.971 --> 05:58.437
he's under Mac and Melba's spell.

05:58.439 --> 05:59.458
I can tell you that.

05:59.483 --> 06:00.706
Yeah, yeah.

06:03.777 --> 06:06.112
D-D-Des, what... what are you doing here?

06:17.188 --> 06:18.724
What's that look for?

06:20.411 --> 06:21.727
I like this.

06:21.729 --> 06:23.395
Hmm?

06:23.397 --> 06:26.866
Waking up together, going out to lunch.

06:26.868 --> 06:30.202
It's nice. We're like a family.

06:30.204 --> 06:31.403
Yeah.

06:31.405 --> 06:33.873
All that's missing is a little one.

06:33.875 --> 06:36.141
After that whole adoption fiasco,

06:36.143 --> 06:39.345
I'm just not sure anymore.
I mean, think about it.

06:39.347 --> 06:41.947
The late nights, the vomiting,
the getting peed on.

06:42.594 --> 06:44.416
It'd be like being back in college.

06:46.420 --> 06:50.956
Besides, I love what we have, you know?

06:50.958 --> 06:52.932
- Just the two of us.
- Yeah.

06:52.934 --> 06:54.314
Totally.

06:54.696 --> 06:56.562
Just the two of us.

07:02.370 --> 07:05.021
I can't believe you came here and
packed me up like I'm a child!

07:05.023 --> 07:06.772
We're not in foster care anymore, Des!

07:06.774 --> 07:09.241
- This is what's best for you.
- You don't know what's best for me.

07:09.243 --> 07:10.710
Y-You don't even know me!

07:10.712 --> 07:12.712
I know your black ass
better than you know yourself,

07:12.714 --> 07:14.180
and you are coming with me.

07:14.182 --> 07:17.449
I told you, Des,
I don't want to cohabitate.

07:17.451 --> 07:19.564
And I told you,

07:19.589 --> 07:21.253
you're obsessed with mahjong.

07:21.255 --> 07:23.856
Dean, I can't let something
happen to you.

07:23.858 --> 07:25.324
Oh, God.

07:25.326 --> 07:28.394
It's... It's... It's... It's...
He's right.

07:28.396 --> 07:29.395
Who's right?

07:29.397 --> 07:31.931
Mac. Mac... h-he used an analogy.

07:31.933 --> 07:34.200
He said that I'm a majestic golden eagle

07:34.202 --> 07:36.001
and that you've been
keeping me in a cage!

07:36.003 --> 07:37.870
Dean, she's just trying to help you out.

07:37.872 --> 07:41.207
How? By controlling me?
Y-You can't stop me from flying!

07:41.209 --> 07:42.808
What kinda white-people shit is that?

07:42.810 --> 07:44.076
It's the truth!

07:44.078 --> 07:45.344
And... And... And... And... And...

07:45.346 --> 07:47.547
And I'm done with being held back!

07:47.549 --> 07:48.680
What?!

07:48.682 --> 07:52.218
I-I-I want you out of my life,
Desna Simms!

07:52.220 --> 07:53.957
Dean!

08:08.436 --> 08:11.704
I just cannot figure out
how the hell this happened.

08:11.706 --> 08:15.041
- I know.
- I mean, was I too overprotective?

08:15.043 --> 08:16.308
You think that's why
he turned his back on me?

08:16.310 --> 08:18.377
I mean, yes, you are overprotective,

08:18.379 --> 08:20.179
but that's not what's going on
right now with Dean.

08:20.181 --> 08:22.381
You have been a Goddamn saint
to him, and you know that.

08:22.383 --> 08:25.384
I have taken care of that boy
my entire life.

08:25.386 --> 08:27.854
- Well, you tell him.
- Always putting him before me,

08:27.856 --> 08:29.388
and he gonna say he don't want me?

08:29.390 --> 08:32.457
He is just going through
something, honey.

08:32.460 --> 08:33.991
H-He'll be back.

08:33.994 --> 08:35.928
Mac and Melba got him, Pol.

08:35.929 --> 08:37.663
What if they don't let him go?

08:37.664 --> 08:39.932
What do Mac and Melba want with
this boy in the first place?

08:39.933 --> 08:42.068
They already got you out of the casino.

08:42.070 --> 08:44.001
I don't know what I'm gonna do

08:44.004 --> 08:46.805
if Virginia can't talk
some sense into him.

08:51.612 --> 08:53.679
Dean, please look at me.

08:53.681 --> 08:55.481
I'm busy.

08:55.483 --> 08:58.217
I know there's some sort of pain
you're feeling.

08:58.219 --> 09:01.287
Uh, my sciatica's cleared up.
Thank you, thank you.

09:01.289 --> 09:03.155
Mahjong!

09:08.229 --> 09:12.231
Let the pain go before you lose
Des and everyone who loves you!

09:12.233 --> 09:14.100
You... you're...
You know what my pain is?

09:14.102 --> 09:17.103
You are! You need to back
the heck up, Virginia!

09:17.105 --> 09:19.438
Let me... Let me out of my cage!

09:19.440 --> 09:22.575
Okay, Dean, I get it.
Listen, you are a falcon.

09:22.577 --> 09:26.178
I'm a majestic golden eagle!
You don't even understand!

09:26.180 --> 09:28.714
Wh-What happened to my Virginia, huh?

09:28.716 --> 09:31.250
Th-The sweet, supportive girl
that I fell in love with,

09:31.252 --> 09:32.985
what happened to her?

09:32.987 --> 09:34.853
Oh, I'll tell you what happened.

09:34.855 --> 09:37.323
I've been livin' in that
raggedy-ass motel with you,

09:37.325 --> 09:39.458
laying on bed bugs, not even trippin'

09:39.460 --> 09:42.128
when you made me label all my thongs!

09:42.130 --> 09:44.663
But you? You've been in here
day and night,

09:44.665 --> 09:46.799
playing with these stupid-ass tiles,

09:46.801 --> 09:48.801
thinking you're...
thinking you're Rain Man!

09:48.803 --> 09:50.573
Virginia, shh!

09:54.742 --> 09:56.408
- Virginia...
- What?

09:56.410 --> 09:58.076
...I don't think I can be with somebody

09:58.078 --> 10:00.146
who treats me with so little respect.

10:02.150 --> 10:05.551
So... you're breaking up with me?

10:07.087 --> 10:08.174
Yeah.

10:09.217 --> 10:11.890
Dean, I love you.

10:11.892 --> 10:12.971
Yeah.

10:13.628 --> 10:15.294
Uh...

10:15.296 --> 10:18.364
Yeah, go away, Virginia. Go away.

10:18.366 --> 10:20.633
I-I'm moving in to the casino.

10:26.240 --> 10:28.908
Hey!

10:35.516 --> 10:38.184
All right, y'all, you come back, okay?

10:39.453 --> 10:41.320
Keep that insurance, uh, updated.

10:41.322 --> 10:43.389
Important.

10:44.060 --> 10:45.724
Hey, Dr. Ken, where you off to?

10:45.726 --> 10:47.726
You got a hot date
with that hot little thing?

10:47.728 --> 10:49.408
What's her name? Gretel?

10:49.410 --> 10:50.596
Gretchen.

10:50.598 --> 10:52.264
You know, to be honest,

10:52.266 --> 10:54.266
I can barely afford to take her out.

10:54.268 --> 10:56.602
You know, this whole legit rehab thing

10:56.604 --> 10:59.605
is seriously threatening
my baller status.

10:59.607 --> 11:01.474
Come on, now, Dr. Ken.

11:01.476 --> 11:03.609
We are... We are changin' people.

11:03.611 --> 11:06.278
We're... We're changin' the world.

11:06.280 --> 11:08.280
I don't care about the world.

11:08.282 --> 11:10.149
I care about me. Okay?

11:10.151 --> 11:11.950
I'm a desirable commodity.

11:11.952 --> 11:13.752
And you know, Peter Pain is hiring.

11:13.754 --> 11:15.688
So if things don't start
to pick up at the clinic,

11:15.690 --> 11:18.090
I'm gonna have to seek greener pastures.

11:18.092 --> 11:19.758
You've been warned.

11:19.760 --> 11:21.427
Don't warn <i> me,</i> boy.

11:24.833 --> 11:26.632
How about you, Miss Brenda?

11:26.634 --> 11:29.368
- You got any complaints?
- No, I'm great.

11:29.370 --> 11:31.720
Sober as a nun on Easter Sunday.

11:31.722 --> 11:32.893
Hmm.

11:32.895 --> 11:35.374
Problem is, without my rum and coke,

11:35.376 --> 11:38.377
I don't know what to do
with myself anymore.

11:38.379 --> 11:41.114
Well, Goddamn.

11:42.517 --> 11:46.853
I-I-I gotta say, I think that
way sometimes myself, you know?

11:47.440 --> 11:49.818
What say you let me...

11:50.258 --> 11:52.591
show you a good time?

11:59.067 --> 12:00.867
Well?

12:02.019 --> 12:06.072
I tried to do my thing
with Dean, but it didn't work.

12:06.074 --> 12:07.740
W-What happened?

12:07.742 --> 12:09.341
He broke up with me.

12:09.343 --> 12:11.343
He broke off the engagement? Come here.

12:11.345 --> 12:13.479
I'm sorry. I tried, Des. I'm sorry.

12:13.481 --> 12:16.415
I really, really tried to help.

12:16.886 --> 12:19.618
Listen, it's not your fault, okay?

12:19.620 --> 12:22.688
Well, tell us what happened.

12:22.690 --> 12:26.092
Uh, well, he...

12:26.855 --> 12:29.095
He said that I hold him back.

12:31.232 --> 12:33.699
I'm so heartbroken, you guys.

12:33.701 --> 12:35.634
It hurts so bad.

12:35.636 --> 12:38.036
China Doll, you don't deserve this, okay?

12:38.038 --> 12:41.039
And... And as soon as we're on
the other side of all of this,

12:41.041 --> 12:42.575
we got you.

12:42.577 --> 12:45.043
We will all get together
and eat our feelings and...

12:45.045 --> 12:47.446
- Oh, hell yeah. Flamin' Hot Cheetos.
- Mm-hmm.

12:47.448 --> 12:49.248
- Yep.
- "Love and Hip Hop" marathons.

12:49.250 --> 12:51.383
- Cornish hens.
- Well...

12:51.385 --> 12:53.252
All of it. But right now,

12:53.254 --> 12:54.720
baby girl, you've got to pull up,

12:54.722 --> 12:57.055
'cause we've got to figure out
what to do about Dean.

12:57.057 --> 12:59.191
- Okay?
- Okay.

13:04.265 --> 13:05.531
- Hey.
- Hey.

13:05.533 --> 13:07.270
Come on in.

13:08.803 --> 13:09.936
Ooh, whoa.

13:11.139 --> 13:14.072
My daughter is livin' large, huh?

13:14.074 --> 13:15.942
Well...

13:15.944 --> 13:18.311
Little bit.

13:19.413 --> 13:21.213
How you feeling?

13:21.701 --> 13:23.316
Like shit.

13:24.418 --> 13:26.218
What about you?

13:26.220 --> 13:27.486
Lost my job.

13:27.488 --> 13:29.822
Calvin, I'm... I'm so sorry.

13:29.824 --> 13:31.157
Come sit down.

13:31.159 --> 13:35.494
Yeah, the firm didn't believe my story.

13:35.496 --> 13:37.029
They think I drugged myself.

13:37.031 --> 13:39.832
They don't believe
those lunatics drugged me.

13:39.834 --> 13:42.835
If it wasn't for you,
I'd go right to the cops.

13:42.837 --> 13:45.838
But those assholes messed up my life,

13:46.284 --> 13:47.840
and they're ruining yours.

13:48.776 --> 13:51.444
Not just me. They got Dean.

13:51.446 --> 13:53.980
He stopped talking to me.

13:53.982 --> 13:56.315
I don't know what I'm gonna do.

13:56.317 --> 13:57.820
Hey...

13:58.453 --> 14:00.853
It'll be all right, hear?

14:33.821 --> 14:36.288
H-Hello?

14:36.290 --> 14:38.424
What's up? I haven't heard from you.

14:38.426 --> 14:41.027
Yeah, just been...

14:41.029 --> 14:42.991
going through some stuff.

14:43.866 --> 14:45.698
Hey, are you okay?

14:45.700 --> 14:47.233
Yeah, I-I guess.

14:47.235 --> 14:49.368
Look, what's wrong?

14:49.789 --> 14:52.104
<i>Look, if you want to talk, I'm free.</i>

14:59.179 --> 15:00.312
He'll be here in a second.

15:00.314 --> 15:02.381
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

15:03.651 --> 15:05.784
Oh. What the heck?!

15:05.786 --> 15:07.920
I-I thought you said
mahjong master Zhao Jian

15:07.922 --> 15:09.388
wanted to meet me.

15:09.390 --> 15:10.989
- You're a liar.
- Dean,

15:10.991 --> 15:14.460
our father has a home in Sanibel
Island, a beach house.

15:14.462 --> 15:16.462
He wants us to live together as a family.

15:16.464 --> 15:18.330
It's too late for that now.

15:18.332 --> 15:20.533
Dean, listen to me.

15:20.535 --> 15:23.001
Okay, this is our chance
at a normal life.

15:23.003 --> 15:25.003
You've always wanted me
out of a life of crime.

15:25.005 --> 15:27.205
I-I-I already have a life now,
and I'm... and I'm happy.

15:27.207 --> 15:29.942
Why can't you just accept that?
I-It's not always about you.

15:29.944 --> 15:31.944
You... You can't always
get what you want.

15:31.946 --> 15:35.081
What <i> I</i> want? I gave up my life
to take care of you.

15:35.083 --> 15:37.884
Just because I'm autistic,
that doesn't mean you have to control me!

